To enable the offline feature, ensure the following configurations are set up. These configurations do not need to be completed in a specific order but are necessary for the seamless functioning of offline mode. Mandatory configurations Offline Enablement by Register Type This feature allows you to enable or disable Offline Mode for specific register types within the POS system. By default, Offline Mode is disabled for all registers. To enable or configure Offline Mode by register type, follow these steps: Navigate to the MUP UI: Application Configuration > Manage POS Configuration > POS Configuration > POS Store Configuration > Store Common Config > Offline Supported Register Types. Select the specific register types you want to support Offline Mode. This configuration can be applied at both the location and organization levels. User Role Grants for Accessing Offline Features and MUP UI in Manhattan Active® Omni POS To access offline features in the Manhattan Active® Omni POS application , grant the following permissions to the user. Grant Purpose Type ui::posservice::menu::pos-cartv2 Gives access to POS 2.0 Store App UI ui::pos::offline::manualswitch Gives access to manually switch to offline Store App UI omui::menu::posOfflineConfigurations Gives access to the offline parent menu in MUP MUP UI omui::backoffice::menu::OfflineTemplates Gives access to the offline templates in MUP MUP UI omui::backoffice::menu::OfflineTransactions Gives access to the offline templates in MUP MUP UI omui::backoffice::menu::OfflineExportMaster Gives access to check the overall status of the offline export for a store MUP UI omui::backoffice::menu::ExportJobMaster Gives access to check the details of the specific run of offline exports MUP UI omui::menu::managePosConfiguration Gives access to enable offline for the register type MUP UI omui::receipt::menu::ReceiptArtifacts Gives access to check the details of receipt artifacts used offline, such as receipt logo MUP UI (To enable offline) omui::devicemanagement::menu::RegisterInfo::read Gives access to the register info entity, which has data related to offline enablement at the device level MUP UI ui::pos::cart::reprintlasttransaction::admin Gives access to enable reprint last offline transaction while Offline Store App UI User PIN Retailers need to set up PIN credentials for all users in the store who access the Manhattan Active® Omni POS application when the store is offline. Just as a valid user ID and password are required to run the Manhattan Active® Omni POS application in normal Cloud Connected mode, a valid user ID and PIN are required to log in to the offline mode of the application. Use the following navigation to set up the user PIN: Omnifacade >> User >> select username >> User PIN Offline Data export To ensure seamless order processing in offline mode, caching item and price details on the local device is essential. This involves downloading and regularly refreshing all the data required for offline and item caching from the central server to the local device. Below are the steps to create a specific scheduler job for regularly exporting this data to the cloud storage. Creating the job processes is one-time task carried out during organization creation. Allow some time before concluding that the export status is stuck. ItemWithPrice (ARI - 2025-03), Promotion (only supported on Windows devices), and BundleData (ARI - 2025-06) exports may not be enabled in all environments, depending on the ARI and configuration settings. Status for these will be in INITIATED status if they are not enabled. These exports are valid only for the 7 days starting from the date of the export. After that, these exports are not used even if the status is SUCCESS. The export process progresses through various status listed below. Refer to the Troubleshooting Guide for help with any export-related issues. Status Description Troubleshooting Guide INITIATED The export process has been initiated. This indicates the API has received the request and triggered the start of the export workflow. Troubleshoot exports in INITIATED status STARTED The export process is actively running. The system has begun generating export files. Troubleshoot exports in STARTED status GENERATION_SUCCESS Export file generation completed successfully. The resulting ZIP files have been created and stored in the object store. Troubleshoot exports in GENERATION_SUCCESS status NO_DATA No exportable data was found. The export process was completed without generating any files due to a lack of relevant data. Troubleshoot exports in NO_DATA status GENERATION_FAILURE Export file generation failed. ZIP files could not be created or uploaded to the object store due to an error during processing. Troubleshoot exports in GENERATION_FAILURE status COMPRESSED The export data has been successfully compressed into ZIP files. However, the upload to cloud storage is still pending. Troubleshoot exports in COMPRESSED status FAILURE A general export process failure occurred. This could be due to an error in initiating the process or an exception during export execution. Troubleshoot exports in FAILURE status END_OF_LIFE_TIMEOUT The export process timed out after 24 hours of monitoring. This prevents indefinite tracking of exports that may have stalled. Troubleshoot exports in END_OF_LIFE_TIMEOUT status UPLOAD_INPROGRESS The system consolidates and uploads all generated ZIP files. This status will remain until the consolidated upload is completed. Troubleshoot exports in UPLOAD_INPROGRESS status SUCCESS The export process was completed successfully. All individual export files and the final consolidated ZIP have been generated and uploaded without issues. Troubleshoot exports in SUCCESS status Note: Alternatively, the MUP UI can be used to access the data at {{url}}/om/dm/screen/backoffice/OfflineExportMaster The maximum supported export file sizes for enabling offline availability may vary based on the device: iPhone SE (3rd Gen, 4GB RAM): Supports export files up to 50MB iPhone 15 (6GB RAM): Supports export files up to 250MB Within these limits, users can download data and continue using the application seamlessly in offline mode. Short Device ID Generation The following API should be used to generate short device IDs for all existing devices. This is a one-time activity performed during the creation of the organization for the customer. API details for Short Device ID Generation HTTP Method: GET API:{{url}}/devicemanagement/api/devicemanagement/deviceInfo/generateShortDeviceId User to be used to generate token: The user must be an organization user with authorisation to run the API and set ups Barcode Rule change to Identify Offline Orders In Manhattan Active® Omni POS 2.0 Transaction IDs differ based on whether orders are processed online or offline. Online transactions are identified by a 21-character transaction ID. However, for POS 2.0 offline orders, which operate at the device level, a 4-character short device ID is appended which extends the transaction ID length to 25 characters. It is important to note that this format change applies exclusively to POS 2.0 offline orders; online orders in POS 2.0 continue to use the original 21-character transaction ID format. To ensure accurate identification of sales transactions through barcode scanning for POS 2.0, the barcode rule for SALE_TRANSACTION_CONDITION_RULE should be updated. This update enables the system to identify a barcode as a sale transaction if the length of the transaction ID is either 21 or 25 characters. The following example serves as a base implementation for updating the barcode rule. Please do not directly replicate this example without first reviewing and analyzing your existing rule configuration. Many customers may have already made modifications to their rules. It is essential to assess the current setup and make adjustments accordingly to ensure compatibility and functionality. Retrieving the Existing Barcode Rule: This is used to retrieve the ConditionValue from the response for further modification. Use the below API to retrieve the existing barcode rule configuration. API to retrieve the existing barcode rule HTTP Method: GET API: {{url}}/barcode/api/rules/ruleCondition?query=RuleConditionId='SALE_TRANSACTION_CONDITION_RULE' User to be used to generate Token :The user must be an organization user with authorisation to run the API and set ups. Modifying the Barcode Rule:This helps in modifying the ConditionValue to include the logic for identifying barcode lengths of both 21 and 25 characters, which are used for offline orders in POS 2.0. Use the following sample request payload as a base implementation. API and sample payload request modify the barcode rule HTTP Method: POST API:{{url}}/barcode/api/rules/ruleCondition/save { "RuleConditionId": "SALE_TRANSACTION_CONDITION_RULE", "ConditionValue": "{\"logicalOperator\":\"and\",\"conditions\":[{\"expression\":{\"logicalOperator\":\"or\",\"conditions\":[{\"lhs\":{\"operandType\":\"attribute\",\"attribute\":\"barcodeIdentificationDTO.text\",\"methodDefinition\":{\"methodName\":\"startsWith\",\"methodArgs\":\"\\\"1\\\"\"}},\"rhs\":{\"operandType\":\"constant\",\"value\":true},\"operator\":\"=\"},{\"lhs\":{\"operandType\":\"attribute\",\"attribute\":\"barcodeIdentificationDTO.text\",\"methodDefinition\":{\"methodName\":\"startsWith\",\"methodArgs\":\"\\\"01\\\"\"}},\"rhs\":{\"operandType\":\"constant\",\"value\":true},\"operator\":\"=\"}]}},{\"expression\":{\"logicalOperator\":\"or\",\"conditions\":[{\"lhs\":{\"operandType\":\"attribute\",\"attribute\":\"barcodeIdentificationDTO.length\"},\"rhs\":{\"operandType\":\"constant\",\"value\":\"21\"},\"operator\":\"=\"},{\"lhs\":{\"operandType\":\"attribute\",\"attribute\":\"barcodeIdentificationDTO.length\"},\"rhs\":{\"operandType\":\"constant\",\"value\":\"25\"},\"operator\":\"=\"}]}}]}" } For existing customers, perform an impact analysis to evaluate the effects of the new offline order format on any systems relying on transaction number lengths. Update any affected systems to accommodate the new format accordingly. Localization Configuration for Offline To support localization in Manhattan Active® Omni POS offline mode, complete the following steps to configure language bundles, user locale, item localization, and receipt templates. Enable Offline Bundle Export Ensure the offline export process includes translation bundles and localized content by enabling the EnableBundleDataExport flag.This exports the required localization data to the offline device.Refer to the Trigger Export section to enable this flag in the export process. Ensure 'OfflineEntityExportEventBackofficeMSGType' is present in your profile for both inbound and outbound message types. Set User Locale Navigate to: Omnifacade → Master Data → Manage Security → User. Select the relevant user and assign a Locale ID. This configuration determines which language bundle the POS will use for that user in offline mode. Item Localization To support localization of item-related data such as description, color, and size in offline mode, ensure that the following structure is properly configured in the offline export template: "LocalizedData": { "LanguageKey": null, "ShortDescription": null, "Color": null, "Size": null Below is the base offline export template for your reference: offline export template { "TemplateId": "OfflineExportTemplate", "BaseEntity": "Item", "TemplateJson": { "ItemId": null, "DepartmentName": null, "DepartmentNumber": null, "Size": null, "Color": null, "IsHazmat": null, "ShortDescription": null, "TaxCode": null, "SmallImageURI": null, "ColorImageURI": null, "ProductSubClass": null, "IsGiftCard": null, "ProductClass": null, "BaseUOM": null, "Style": null, "ItemCode": { "Type": null, "Value": null }, "SellingAttributes": { "TaxCode": null, "IsTaxOverrideable": null, "IsPriceOverrideable": null, "IsDiscountable": null }, "HandlingAttributes": { "IsHazmat": null, "HazmatCode": null }, "LocalizedData": { "LanguageKey": null, "ShortDescription": null, "Color": null, "Size": null }, "EntityLabels": null, "LinkedItem": { "LinkedItemId": null, "LinkedItemType": { "LinkType": { "LinkTypeId": null }, "LinkedItemTypeId": null } } } } Receipt Localization To support localized receipt generation in Manhattan Active® Omni POS offline mode, ensure the following configurations are in place. This enables proper rendering of localized headers, footers, logos, and content based on the user's configured locale.To enable receipt localization in offline mode according to the configured user locale, follow the steps below: Configure the Receipt Template Each supported locale should have a dedicated receipt template. Use the following format to define the template ID: "TemplateId": "ReceiptTemplate_<locale-code>" For Example,  the French (Canada) locale, the template ID should be: "TemplateId": "ReceiptTemplate_fr" The Template Body content must be localized as per the corresponding locale. If a localized receipt template is not configured, the system falls back to the default template. In such cases, receipt generation uses the user’s configured locale (via Locale ID) to apply translations, if available. Configure Receipt Parameters in Receipt Params To render the correct localized content in the printed receipt (such as header, footer, and logos), you must define the ReceiptLanguage in the receipt params as shown below: Below is the sample: "ReceiptHeader": "Bienvenue chez Omni", "ReceiptFooter": "Nous serons heureux de rembourser ou d’échanger tout nouvel article", "ReceiptLanguage": "fr" Information Tax Configuration In the Tax rate Configuration (under Advanced Tax Rate V2), set the tax rate as 'is Informational' = true. In POS Store Configurations > Store Common Config, set “Primary Tax as Info” = TRUE. Define the VAT Tax Code in the Tax rate configuration (Under Advanced Tax Rate V2). This is optional. Enable “Enable Persistent VAT Tax Codes” under POS Store Configurations > Receipt Config If VAT Tax Code is defined, it will always be printed on the receipt, regardless of the “Enable Persistent VAT Tax Codes” flag. If not defined, when “Enable Persistent VAT Tax Codes” is disabled, the system will automatically generate a VAT Tax Code on the fly. When “Enable Persistent VAT Tax Codes” is enabled, the system will not print any VAT Tax Code in the receipt because none are predefined. For more details, refer Local Tax and POS Tax Configuration This feature has mandatory offline receipt template changes. Please copy or save the latest base offlineTemplate for  ReceiptTemplate before enabling this feature. Ensure that the base seed data receipt template is imported to display Informational Tax details correctly on offline receipts. Also, verify that the appropriate tax code is configured in the Advanced Tax Rate V2 configuration to support accurate tax calculations and display. Offline Promotion Configuration (Windows Only) Prerequisite: Before configuring POS 2.0 Offline Promotions, ensure that the POS Classic Edge server is not running and has been completely shut down. All job schedules related to the Edge server should also be disabled. Exclude OpenJDK from Firewall Restrictions: Ensure OpenJDK is not blocked by the Windows Firewall. This is necessary for the local Promotion service to operate correctly. To enable offline promotions, you must install the POS application using Windows PowerShell (Run as Administrator). This step is required to install the ManhSCALE certificate, which is used by the local promotion server to function correctly. Ensure Offline Export Job includes "EnablePromotionExport":true, refer to Trigger Export Setting Up Environment Variables for Offline Promotions To enable offline promotions, specific environment variables must be configured on the Windows system where the Manhattan Active® Omni POS application is installed. Environment Variables Setup Instructions Open File Explorer and right-click on "This PC" in the left-hand panel, then select Properties. In the System Properties window: Click on Advanced System Settings. Click on Environment Variables. Under System Variables, click New. Enter the required belwo values: Variable Name: storeappconfig Variable Value: OFFLINE_PROMO_ENABLED=true Click OK in the System Variables window. Click OK in the Environment Variables window. Click Apply in the System Properties window. Close all windows and launch the store application. When configuring environment variables, make sure to click OK on the active dialog box and on all parent windows to apply the changes correctly. It may take up to 5 minutes for the offline promotion service to start after installation. Please allow sufficient time for the service to initialize before proceeding. Verifying Offline Promotion Service Status After completing the installation and configuration steps, follow the steps below to confirm that the offline promotion service is running: Navigate to the Register Information page within the POS application. If the service is ready, the Offline Promotion Service Status will indicate that promotions are available for offline use. If not, the Offline Promo Service Unavailability Reason will display the reason for failure. Refer to the Register Information section for more details. Custom Configurations Customizing Export Data The following is a sample for customizing item export data. Please ensure to follow the same steps when customizing other export data.. Customizing Item Data Prerequisite: Ensure extended attributes are created on the item entity for any fields to be included in item caching. Retrieve the Offline Export Template:Use the following API to retrieve the Offline Export Template, which contains predefined fields for item data. Customizing Payment option To enhance payment options availability in offline mode, a user exit has been integrated into the {{url}}/payment/api/payment/availablePaymentOptionsOffline API. This feature enables users to filter available payment options effectively. In proactive documentation, users can quickly locate the user exit by searching for: Payment:Payment:UserExit This enhancement allows for tailored customization of payment methods when the system operates in offline mode. Offline Receipt Customization In the  offline system, Mustache templates are used for receipt generation. The template is combined with receipt data, such as order and location details, to produce the final receipt output. The receipt template is stored in the Offline Template entity within the Backoffice component.This template has to be overridden to customise the offline receipt .To customize the offline receipt, follow these steps: Retrieve the Existing Receipt Template Data: URL: {{url}}/backoffice/api/backoffice/offlineTemplate?query=TemplateId='ReceiptTemplate' HTTP Method: GET Note: You can unescape the data before making modifications. Modify the Template as Required: Take the online print receipt output and convert it to an offline template. Use the appropriate tags to align and format the receipt data accordingly. More details on the appropriate tags and formatting can be found below. Validate the Modified Template: Use a tool like Mustache Tester to validate the modified template with a sample order JSON. Save the Modified Template: URL: {{url}}/backoffice/api/backoffice/offlineTemplate/save HTTP Method: POST Request Body: (Replace the value of TemplateData in the request with the customized template) Note: The data should be in string format. If you have unescaped the data earlier, please escape it before saving. Always use the TemplateId value as ReceiptTemplate. { "TemplateId": "ReceiptTemplate", "TemplateData": "<Add customzied template data here>" } Reload the Application: Relogin to the app and navigate to the ‘Cart Next Gen’ screen to download the latest template to the device. Validate the Print Receipt: Perform an offline transaction to ensure that the receipt prints correctly with the customized template. Customization Options for Receipt Templates Tags and Attributes Mustache is a logicless template engine used in offline for receipt generation. To support formatting, size, and overflow of elements, we provide tags along with attributes. Each element in the response is separated by an <element> tag. This tag represents an individual element in the response set, allowing users to specify the length, alignment, and formatting of each element. It also manages overflow when an element exceeds the specified size limit. Supported Attributes: Size: Used to specify the size of each element. If no size is provided, the default value is 40 characters. Align: Supports the alignment of elements based on the size. Supported alignment values are center, right and left. Format: Supports formatting of elements, such as amount formatting (e.g., currency). Overflow: Sometimes, some elements might exceed the 40-character limit. By default, if the overflow tag is not provided, the code will truncate the data within the elements to fit within the 40-character limit. If the overflow tag is provided, the code will handle overflowing the lines based on how many lines can be split based on the 40-character limit.
